author: @brunobucciaralick3914
text:
Song? Amazing. Yuri? Beautiful. Proud? AF. But the music video.. Each set on its own was great, I liked it, but, and I can already feel the hate from all producer people, the way it kept changing between each set and all those close ups? I don't know, weren't my thing. It was..hard to watch? Dunno, there are different ways to film and record things, obviously it's impossible to like everything. Either way, I did not expect this to be THIS much of a an amazing song since Yuri was always the one that was just...there, for me. But now she's shining and owning a whole song on her own (I'm not a sone so I don't know if she's ever done something on her own before^^) and she definitely found her way into my heart! I think I'll stick with the live performances though as they're more visually pleasing to my eyes^^
Fighting Yuri and let's get her as many views as possible! â™¥

author: @shimishimi75
text:
Eh dont judge me. Just voicing my oppinion.

I'm glad SM finally acknowledged and giving a chance for non main vocal ish member to do solo promo.

However I afraid this is not done with fully capacity and done for the sake of filling the gap, waiting  for snsd to finay make their comeback (since it is hard to keep ot8 together).

The song is meh.. really not as what I expected. With Sunmi killing every single solo comeback, Yuri will be compare to her, and this is farr from Sunmi quality. Song wise..

I understand that this is a new sound. However is this all? This is not showcasing anything of Yuri's full capability.

The dance just fine.

And what I really complain about is...  SM IS VERY BAD AT PROMOTING SEXY CONCEPT TO THEIR ARTIST.

Yuri once a sexy icon of kpop. She maintains her body well and not afraid showing her cleavage. But this is just a poorly done choreo and concept. Whoever saying that Yuri will be the next Lee Hyori with this video is totally blind.

The only thing I want to appreciate is Yuri's visual and this video editing, background is no joke.. really cool stuff..

Outfit not so much. Really weird rainbow costume and ear rings.

Share your thoughts guys.. no hatee just lovee..

SM Need to understand and follow the trend. I really hope Oh GG and solo promo will go well. Please give them good song, cause in the end thet are a siger not just another idol.

author: @elitenurseangie2460
text: SNSD started it all for me. I can't believe I discovered them 8 years ago already... it doesn't feel like it honestly. No matter which group I was into I would always come back to them (even after BTS wrecked my life), they are true queens in my heart. The GG of yesterday is still GG. They all have grown a lot a matured and everyone of them has found their own style and can be a solo artist. I'm still waiting for Sunny to drop something (and maybe Sooyoung too). For the time being, I'm happy that this goof ball has a solo debut and the melody is already stuck in my head, it's so catchy!  And that dance move with the arms was well found too! I don't why but it fits xD Let's stream this along with Lil Touch Sones! We shouldn't get lazy when our queens are still active after 11 years! I can't wait for Oh!GG to comeback with something else (and promote on music shows this time)! I hope we'll have a comeback with the whole team next year.
